---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';

import ContactCTA from '../components/ContactCTA.astro';
import Hero from '../components/Hero.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="About | Natalia Kuchta" description="About Natalia Kuchta">
    <div class="stack gap-20">
        <main class="wrapper about">
            <Hero
                    title="I love travels and programming"
                    tagline="Dive with me into the world of programming and traveling, discovering fascinating corners of the digital universe and adventurous paths of coding. "
            >



                <img src="/assets/walkingOnPlanets.gif" alt="planet"
                     class="object-cover w-full h-96">

            </Hero>

            <section>


                <div class="content">
                    <article class="prose lg:prose-xl dark:text-slate-200 bold 	font-style: normal">
                        <p> Traveling with programming is like bringing your own superhero cape—no matter where you go,
                            you've got the power to debug your way out of any situation. Wi-Fi might be the final boss,
                            but with enough coffee and code, you can conquer anything from a beachfront bungalow to a
                            mountain cabin.
                            Just remember, if your code works on vacation, it’s basically a souvenir!</p>

                        <p>I’m crashing the scene like the world’s one big “cyberpunk” matrix, where every line of code
                            is a new hack in my mission. Here’s how my journey through the global “darknet” full of code
                            and compilers looks, as seen by a true “haxor”:</p>


                        <p> Dubai – My laptop’s now “hot” like a “server farm” in the middle of the desert. Debugging in
                            this heat? My computer has more “overheat warnings” than code. The only “ping” is “ERROR:
                            OVERHEATING” with a lightning bolt beside it.


                        <p> Thailand – Pad Thai? More like “pad bugs.” Between “syntax errors” and “spicy exceptions,”
                            I’m trying to fix my code, not just the spices. Where’s my “debugging sauce”?</p>


                        <p> Bali – Surfing and coding is my new “dual-booting.” I’m trying to “surf” with my laptop, but
                            instead of “high scores,” I’m getting “high fails.” My skills are at “FAIL whale” beta
                            version.
                        <p>


                        <p> Vietnam – “Ping” in a maze of streets? My GPS is more confused than my recursive function.
                            Vietnamese “pho” has more “local variables” than my code, and I’m still searching for a
                            “syntax fix.”</p>


                        <p> Georgia – Debugging with wine in hand? It’s like “code reviews” in “relax mode.” Khachapuri
                            + wine = “optimal configuration” for every “deploy script.”</p>


                        <p> Malaysia – Jungle full of “tropical exceptions.” I’m discovering that the “secret sambal
                            recipe” is the real “key to cracking the code.” “Code cracking” in the tropics is the new
                            standard.</p>


                        <p> Venice – Coding on a gondola? “Avoiding canal errors” is like “handling edge cases” in
                            “extreme” mode. Avoiding “crashes” and “canal falls” is my new hobby.
                        <p>


                        <p> Paris – Coding under the Eiffel Tower is like “coding with croissant.” Every line is like a
                            “high-performance pastry” with “bootstrap” on top. Debugging in the city of love? Now it’s
                            “code chic.”
                        <p>


                        <p> Malta – The view of the blue waters is like a “remote server” with “optimal latency.” The
                            sea breeze? Probably adding a “code refresh” to every “deployment.”
                        <p>


                        <p> Cyprus – Integrating Cypriot lemons and honey with code is like “sweet algorithmic fusion.”
                            “Sweet algorithms” are now “production ready” with a “Cypriot boost.”</p>


                        <p> Bulgaria – Coding in stone houses is like “legacy system debugging” in “historical mode.”
                            Hard errors vs. soft dumplings – now I know how to “code balance” in the “stone age.”</p>


                        <p> Albania – Exploring the nooks of this country is like “unknown vulnerabilities” in my code.
                            I’m discovering that local adventures are as “unexpected” as new “security exploits.”</p>


                        <p>
                            In summary, every “deploy” and “commit” is like a new “phase” in my “cyber-adventure,” with
                            each location as a “new patch” in my “global coding project.” Looking forward to more
                            “hacks” and “exploits” in this “open source” journey!
                        </p>

                        <span>Keep hacking, stay encrypted! 🖥️💣</span>


                        <img src="/assets/pinkwaves.gif" alt="pink-waves">
                    </article>
                </div>



            </section>
            <section>
                <h2 class=" section-title"></h2>
                <div class="content">
                    <p></p>
                </div>
            </section>
            <section>
                <h2 class="section-title"></h2>
                <div class="content">
                    <p></p>
                </div>
            </section>
        </main>

        <ContactCTA/>
    </div>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
    .about {
        display: flex;
        flex-direction: column;
        gap: 3.5rem;
    }

    img {
        margin-top: 1.5rem;
        border-radius: 1.5rem;
        box-shadow: var(--shadow-md);
    }

    section {
        display: flex;
        flex-direction: column;
        gap: 0.5rem;
        color: var(--gray-200);
    }

    .section-title {
        grid-column-start: 1;
        font-size: var(--text-xl);
        color: var(--gray-0);
    }

    .content {
        grid-column: 2 / 4;
        font-size: large;


    }

    .content :global(a) {
        text-decoration: 1px solid underline transparent;
        text-underline-offset: 0.25em;
        transition: text-decoration-color var(--theme-transition);
    }

    .content :global(a:hover),
    .content :global(a:focus) {
        text-decoration-color: currentColor;
    }

    @media (min-width: 50em) {
        .about {
            display: grid;
            grid-template-columns: 1fr 60% 1fr;
        }

        .about > :global(:first-child) {
            grid-column-start: 2;
        }

        section {
            display: contents;
            font-size: var(--text-lg);
        }
    }
</style>
